caption: This Joan of Arc statue is located bronze statue Blvd Saint-Marcel south of Jardin des Plantes. This is the work of French sculptor √âmile-Fran√ßois Chatrousse and was erected here in 1891.  What is interesting about this monument to Joan of Arc is that is not the usual depiction of the French Heroine as a warrior on horseback. Instead you see her standing and looking forward. She holds flag in right hand and her shield in the other while sword is held in scabbard.

Here, no Joan of Arc, ready to go to war, on her proud steed, but on foot and in armor, the standard raised, her eyes raised to the sky, and always ready to fight to drive the English out of France ! We know his tragic end, accused and betrayed by Bishop Cauchon! Beautiful statue of Joan of Arc who proudly brandishes her pointed standard and seems to greet us every time we pass in front of her, reminding us of her illustrious memory and the timeless beauty of the character she embodied for France far beyond the pathetic characters who condemned her...! She has survived in our memory and history will have forgotten her sordid executioners, one of whom, if I remember, had an animal name that just suited him...!
